line_2: In Birds, as well as mortal Folks;

line_1: Nor licks the bounteous Hand, (ev'n Love provokes)
line_2: Nor fisks the Tail, or fawns at gentle Stroaks.

line_1: A worthless Fly the mighty Fish provokes.
line_2: Tho' swift their Pace, tho' Fate attends their Strokes,

line_1: The Miller, whom this most of all provokes,
line_2: See, how's she spent, and sinks beneath their strokes
